.TH PASSPORT-UNLOCKER-HELPER 8 "July 2026" "passport-unlocker 0.1.0" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
passport-unlocker-helper \- restricted privileged helper for Passport Unlocker
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B passport-unlocker-helper
.RB { status | unlock-and-rescan }
.BI --stable-id " STABLE_ID"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B passport-unlocker-helper
is an internal, one-shot helper intended to be invoked through the installed
Polkit policy. It re-discovers and validates the selected USB disk before
performing one fixed protocol operation.
.PP
For
.BR unlock-and-rescan ,
the password is accepted only through the length-prefixed standard-input wire
protocol. Results are emitted as one line of JSON. The helper does not accept
passwords or arbitrary SCSI command bytes as command-line options.
.SH OPERATIONS
.TP
.B status
Query the validated device security state.
.TP
.B unlock-and-rescan
Attempt an unlock, verify the resulting state, and request re-discovery of the
same stable device identity.
.SH SECURITY
This command is not a general-purpose raw SCSI utility. It uses a fixed command
allowlist and must not be exposed as an unrestricted set-user-ID program.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR passport-unlocker (1),
.BR pkexec (1),
.BR polkit (8)

